# Summary
This documentation explains the "Cohort Population Over Time" chart in Amplitude, which tracks how behavioral cohort sizes change over time, displaying the number of users meeting cohort criteria on each day. This feature helps teams identify trends and evaluate the effectiveness of campaigns or releases by visualizing dynamic cohort population changes.

